My idea

Mentorship 
This is a key aspect in learning. We benefit a lot from other people other than reading on our own. Some people understand a concept better than we get it and teach in a certain way that would make others understand it better and remember. Another thing is some mentors have been there before , they can advise beginners on what to do better , mistakes not to make; advise to younger self and that is why we all need mentors.

I have an idea to make this possible and this is to make an app that can help learners find such mentors , learn from them , a mentor with particular interests as them. Also for mentors who want to give back to the community.
I want something simple to start so we can use it in our school.

Features
Signup
Enter preferences

Request mentorship with a message eg am interested about learning loops in python
Before sending a request, ask learners:
What do you want help with?
Your current level?
Goal? 
🎯 Learner User Journey (Your Mentorship App)
🟢 1. Entry Point (First Contact)
Goal: Get the learner into the app
Learner hears about the app (school, friends, poster, WhatsApp)
Opens the app / website
👉 Screen:
“Find the right mentor for you”
CTA: Sign Up / Get Started

📝 2. Sign Up + Preferences (MOST IMPORTANT STEP)
Goal: Understand the learner immediately
Learner fills:
Name / Email / Password
Select Role → Learner
Interests (e.g. Python, Data Science)
Current Level → Beginner / Intermediate / Advanced
Goal (optional but powerful):
“Pass exam”
“Build projects”
“Learn basics”
👉 UX Tip:
 Make this feel like:
“Let’s find the best mentor for you” (not a boring form)

🧠 3. Smart Matching Happens (Behind the Scenes)
System uses their preferences to:
Filter mentors
Rank best matches

🏠 4. Dashboard (Personalized Experience)
Goal: Instant value — no searching needed
Learner sees:
“Mentors matched for you”
List of mentors:
Name
Skills
Level they teach
Short bio
👉 This is your WOW moment

👀 5. View Mentor Profile
Goal: Build trust before requesting
Learner clicks a mentor → sees:
Bio
Skills
Experience
Who they help (e.g. beginners)
Availability (optional)

📩 6. Send Mentorship Request
Goal: Start connection
Learner clicks:
“Request Mentorship”
Fills:
What they need help with
Their goal
Optional message
Example:
“I’m learning Go and struggling with loops. I want to build small projects.”

⏳ 7. Waiting State
Goal: Keep user engaged
System shows:
Request status → Pending
👉 UX Idea:
Suggest other mentors while waiting

✅ ❌ 8. Mentor Response
If Accepted:
🎉 Learner sees:
“Your request was accepted!”
Can now:
Message mentor (future feature)
Schedule session

If Declined:
👉 Show reason (important!):
Busy
Not a good fit
Not their area
Suggest:
“Here are similar mentors”

🔍 9. Explore Option (User Control)
At any time, learner can:
Click “Explore Mentors”
See all mentors
Apply filters:
Skill
Level
Availability

🔁 10. Continuous Use (Retention)
Learner:
Connects with multiple mentors
Learns different skills
Possibly becomes a mentor later 👀

🔥 Visual Flow (Simple)
Sign Up → Preferences → Dashboard (Matches)
      → View Mentor → Send Request
      → Accepted / Declined
      → Explore More Mentors

💡 Key Experience Principles You’re Using
✅ Personalization first
Users don’t feel lost
✅ Low effort
No heavy searching
✅ Feedback loops
Accept / decline improves system
✅ Flexibility
Explore option gives freedom

🧠 Product Insight (Important)
Your app is not just:
“Find mentors”
It is:
“Guide learners to the RIGHT mentor quickly”
That’s what makes it powerful.

